6.33 Assembly Requirement Allocation
Assembly Requirement Allocation includes the following information: complete functional and
physical interface requirements, complete capability to allocate enterprise or external agency
requirements to assembly function or physical design, model based requirement description using
simulation models and models with assigned parametric data. Supporting data including
documetn, authorization, product identification, external definition, and authorization are included.
The class requires the implementation of the following Units of Functionality:
 analytical model;
 analytical representation;
 assembly functional interface requirement;
 assembly functional requirement allocation;
 assembly physical interface requirement;
 assembly physical requirement allocation;
 authorization;
 characteristic;
 document;
 end item identification;
 external definition.
